Document: CubemapArray
Path: godot/classes/class_cubemaparray.rst
Summary: CubemapArray stores multiple Cubemap textures for efficient shader access and is used internally for effects like Sky reflections.

CubemapArray stores an array of Cubemap textures. Each Cubemap must contain a number of textures divisible by 6 (one for each cube face). The primary benefit of CubemapArray is enabling shader access through a single texture reference, allowing multiple Cubemaps to be passed to shaders efficiently. CubemapArray is used internally by Godot for effects like Sky when ProjectSettings.rendering/reflections/sky_reflections/texture_array_reflections is enabled.

To create a CubemapArray, use ImageTextureLayered.create_from_images() on a CubemapArray instance. The required image order follows Godot's coordinate system: X+ (right), X- (left), Y+ (up), Y- (down), Z+ (back), Z- (forward). Supported image layouts include 2×3 (default), 3×2, 1×6, and 6×1. Vertical imports stack layers top-to-bottom, while horizontal layouts arrange them left-to-right.

Note: CubemapArray is not supported in the Compatibility renderer due to graphics API limitations.
